    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' colspan='2'>EVERFROST</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
		<td align='left' class='db' vAlign='top'><img align=right src=''> <p>Everfrost is a snow covered zone which serves the newbie Barbarians of Halas.
It is usually a step before people visit the Gnolls home Blackburrow, but is
still quite a large and diverse zone. From the Barbarian guards which help
fleeing newbies who have overpulled or been trained, the zone is a myriad of
high snow covered walls.</p>
<p>For the low levels around 1 to 4 there are the usual level 1 and 2 mobs that
can be slain for exp, but a warning needed because these are mostly monsters
that will train on you if you don't watch out. Also, another warning for those
low levels out there who like to hunt skeletons for thier bone chips and rusty
weapons, in Everfrost, there are a group of skeletons, known as Vengefulls,
which spawn and can wipe the floor with those below level 8 or 9.</p>
<p>After about level 9 or 10 is reached, one would start heading towards the Orc
camp in the zone. Snow Orcs can be from level 7 to 15, depending on what they
actually are, but be careful to consider everything before you begin to attack
it. The open plains of Everfrost are full of dangers, littered with camps of Ice
Goblins and Snow Orcs, so one must proceed with caution through this zone.</p>
<p>To the southern end of the Everfrost maze, there is the zone to the
Blackburrow, which then leads onto Queynos Hills and the rest of Antonica. One
must take caution when travelling through this as the zone is surrounded by
assorted Gnolls. To the east of the plain is the entrance to Permafrost, there
the infamous Lady Vox can be found.</p>
</td>
		<td width='18%' align='right' class='db' valign='top'><font class=dbti>Zone Information</font><br><a href='http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/forumdisplay.cgi?action=topics&forum=Everfrost&number=191&DaysPrune=5&LastLogin='>Forum</a><br><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/zones.asp?Action=ListByMonsters&SubAction=ShowAll&ZoneId=23'>Monsters</a><br><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/zones.asp?Action=ListItems&SubAction=ShowAll&ZoneId=23'>Items</a><br> <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/maps.asp?Action=Description&Id=23'>Map</a>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td colspan=2>
  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>ZONE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>GOOD LVLING</span><b>, By Zaragoth</b> <small>(2/26/2001)</small><br><br>This zone is great for newbies to lvl in. Barbarian warriors at lvl 7 can take on a Vengeful red soloing with a good weapon and armour and this provides great exp. However, great caution must be taken with the vengefuls. Some can be a bit too powerful and can kill you if their AC is high. Usually Vengeful Soloists are a lot tougher to take on than the others. But with some luck, and good steel and armour, any warrior should be able to take one on. It is advised to have a group if you are lvling by killing vengefuls. But if real experience is wanted, try tackling a baby Mammoth at lvl 8. OUCH! and good luck.
(BTW: got from lvl 1 to 8 in 5 hours, tackling on vengefuls in a group, so this zone is a great newbie zone).<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>YOU FORGOT TO MENTION ...</span><b>, By Aalanack</b> <small>(2/23/2001)</small><br><br>You forgot to mention the high level mobs (giants) here and the entrance to Permafrost.  If you're a newbie/low level non-twink, sometimes you can loot the giant corpses that high levels leave behind for some decent amounts.  Be careful tho, the giants would not be fun to mess with at those levels<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>PART OF EPIC QUEST IN THIS ZONE</span><b>, By Taelamar gallianth</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>This zone is a part of the Druid/ranger Epic quests. You have to forage a certain NO DROP item in this zone.<br><hr size='1'></td>
